gomodel:SYNGO_4521  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 2 shows that OGT regulates the synaptic expression of AMPA receptors by immunoblot analysis of total and surface-expressed of AMPA receptor subunits. GluA2 and GluA3 are significantly downregulated in OGT KO animals.\nFig. 3 shows that deletion (Immuno-cytochemistry) of OGT leads to fewer surface GluA2 clusters.\n\n15/02/2021 Dnyanada: The surface expression of GluA2 and GluA3 subunit was reduced in mature OGT KO cortical neurons. Figure 4 and 5 demonstrate a reduction in the number of mature spines in OGT KO neurons. However, as the paper does not causally (and chronologically) link these two effects, a separate annotation for the term \"regulation of synapse maturation\" was made (SynGO ID: 4525).. Experimental description: We developed a mouse model where OGT was deleted\ngenetically from mature brain neurons in vivo... (p. 1685) (cKO: PMID 26989246)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4521" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

